      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STENO (8) continued her good form when she came from this barrier to place last start. Her previous two attempts at this circuit and distance resulted in a Sibelia Stakes win and a second to Captains Mistress in the G1 Queen Elizabeth II Mile. Reliable and can go close with even luck. LUX AETERNA (1) made a successful hit-and-run visit to Albion Park last start, leading from this barrier and digging deep to get home narrowly. Owns a strong strike rate here so can give a sight. SUGAR PIE HONEY (4) is back in form having come from wider barriers to win her last two outings at this circuit and distance, beating STENO last time. Could strike again. TOKYO ROSE NZ (7) led and faded last start but generally races well over the mile here so is worth another chance. Last-start winner SNAP SHOT NZ (6) jumps in grade but is making progress.",
